1045
01:02:45.566 --> 01:02:49.066
latter half of this session where we're looking at risk factors for

1046
01:02:49.206 --> 01:02:49.786
survival.

1047
01:02:52.426 --> 01:02:55.866
I have no financial relationships to disclose.

1048
01:02:56.706 --> 01:03:00.626
So, some of you may know that colorectal cancer is the second leading

1049
01:03:00.646 --> 01:03:04.066
cause of cancer-related mortality in the US, and

1050
01:03:04.566 --> 01:03:07.446
if you were at the Advances in Survivorship

1051
01:03:08.326 --> 01:03:09.666
session earlier today,

1052
01:03:10.666 --> 01:03:14.306
Dr. Kathy Eng actually mentioned that it is now the

1053
01:03:14.466 --> 01:03:18.066
leading cause of cancer-related mortality among younger men.

1054
01:03:18.686 --> 01:03:22.586
And just remember that, because it's going to come back in my presentation as well.

1055
01:03:23.546 --> 01:03:26.946
Patients with colorectal cancer are at a higher risk for

1056
01:03:27.006 --> 01:03:28.486
malnutrition and

1057
01:03:29.326 --> 01:03:32.986
also metabolic dysfunction. And this is particularly

1058
01:03:33.046 --> 01:03:36.906
common in older adults because older adults are inherently at a higher

1059
01:03:36.946 --> 01:03:38.246
risk for malnutrition.

1060
01:03:39.186 --> 01:03:42.466
Such a cancer-related malnutrition then can lead to increased

1061
01:03:42.886 --> 01:03:46.866
metabolism, and that results in an increased resting energy

1062
01:03:46.926 --> 01:03:47.726
expenditure,

1063
01:03:48.586 --> 01:03:52.546
and that may lead to conditions such as cachexia if it's combined

1064
01:03:52.606 --> 01:03:56.366
with muscle loss. And that's why

1065
01:03:56.426 --> 01:04:00.346
increased metabolism has been associated with several clinical

1066
01:04:00.406 --> 01:04:03.756
outcomes, including postoperative complications as well as

1067
01:04:03.786 --> 01:04:07.546
survival. Now there's various different ways to

1068
01:04:07.566 --> 01:04:11.086
measure metabolism in a patient. There's more

1069
01:04:11.486 --> 01:04:13.526
objective methods like calorimetry.

1070
01:04:14.066 --> 01:04:17.566
You probably have heard of the biophysical

1071
01:04:17.606 --> 01:04:21.426
impedance. One very simple way to

1072
01:04:21.706 --> 01:04:25.366
predict your metabolic rate is through these predictive

1073
01:04:25.426 --> 01:04:28.706
equations that have been developed over the years, and

1074
01:04:30.066 --> 01:04:33.766
we used one of the predictive equations to test

1075
01:04:34.266 --> 01:04:36.446
the association with survival. So

1076
01:04:37.546 --> 01:04:40.326
basal metabolic rate essentially represents your

1077
01:04:40.986 --> 01:04:42.866
essential daily expenditure,

1078
01:04:43.666 --> 01:04:46.546
which is required to maintain your bodily functions.

1079
01:04:47.106 --> 01:04:50.666
Again, it can be measured objectively, but it can be predicted through various

1080
01:04:50.706 --> 01:04:54.636
equations as well. In the current literature, high

1081
01:04:54.986 --> 01:04:58.346
basal metabolic rate has been associated with several

1082
01:04:58.686 --> 01:05:02.586
cancers, such as colorectal cancer, esophageal, and other

1083
01:05:02.626 --> 01:05:06.166
hormone-related cancers, and this has also been shown in large

1084
01:05:07.006 --> 01:05:10.886
epidemiologic cohorts, such as the EPIC cohort with half a million

1085
01:05:11.246 --> 01:05:11.926
individuals.

1086
01:05:12.866 --> 01:05:16.246
However, the association between basal metabolic rate

1087
01:05:16.726 --> 01:05:19.406
and cancer survival is as yet unclear.

1088
01:05:20.286 --> 01:05:23.636
We found only two studies, both done in

1089
01:05:23.726 --> 01:05:27.336
Asia and in gastric cancer patients, where these

1090
01:05:27.346 --> 01:05:31.206
predictive basal metabolic rate equations were used to

1091
01:05:31.266 --> 01:05:33.346
assess the relationship with survival.

1092
01:05:33.806 --> 01:05:37.306
And so we were just curious to understand whether this can be

1093
01:05:37.706 --> 01:05:40.946
used as a prognostic marker in colorectal cancer patients.

1094
01:05:43.086 --> 01:05:43.186
Oh,

1095
01:05:44.006 --> 01:05:44.426
sorry.

1096
01:05:45.806 --> 01:05:49.086
So our objective with this project was to investigate the

1097
01:05:49.126 --> 01:05:52.486
association of basal metabolic rate that we

1098
01:05:52.546 --> 01:05:55.986
captured at or around cancer

1099
01:05:56.026 --> 01:05:59.846
diagnosis with overall, as well as colorectal

1100
01:05:59.906 --> 01:06:03.426
cancer-specific survival, and we evaluated

1101
01:06:03.466 --> 01:06:06.326
differences by age of onset and sex.

1102
01:06:08.126 --> 01:06:11.506
So we did this in the prospective

1103
01:06:11.606 --> 01:06:14.366
