1108
01:06:30.486 --> 01:06:34.186
The centers are listed here. The coordinating center for the colorectal

1109
01:06:34.286 --> 01:06:36.646
study is at the Huntsman Cancer Institute.

1110
01:06:37.526 --> 01:06:41.406
And so thus far, we have recruited over 4,300

1111
01:06:41.466 --> 01:06:45.446
patients with colorectal cancer in this cohort, and we

1112
01:06:45.466 --> 01:06:47.706
have extensively phenotyped these patients.

1113
01:06:50.110 --> 01:06:53.750
So for this project, we used data on

1114
01:06:53.950 --> 01:06:57.410
3,760 patients from the COLO-CAIR study.

1115
01:06:57.450 --> 01:07:00.950
We used patients from all sides and all

1116
01:07:00.990 --> 01:07:02.370
stages of cancer.

1117
01:07:03.190 --> 01:07:07.010
Our primary exposure was basal metabolic rate using

1118
01:07:07.050 --> 01:07:10.690
these predictive equations. I'm not going to go over

1119
01:07:11.310 --> 01:07:15.250
how this predictive equation works and how the BMR was

1120
01:07:15.310 --> 01:07:18.990
calculated, but I put the image here so that you can see the

1121
01:07:19.010 --> 01:07:22.870
