1122
01:07:22.970 --> 01:07:26.470
of weight and height, and there's different loading

1123
01:07:26.530 --> 01:07:30.510
factors by sex and age. And that

1124
01:07:30.530 --> 01:07:34.330
represents how the metabolic needs of an

1125
01:07:34.370 --> 01:07:37.910
individual change over their life course, and of course,

1126
01:07:37.930 --> 01:07:40.710
differences by sex.

1127
01:07:42.230 --> 01:07:45.950
And then our outcomes were overall and cancer-specific

1128
01:07:46.030 --> 01:07:46.530
survival.

1129
01:07:47.390 --> 01:07:51.159
We used adjusted Cox proportional hazards

